===Etymology===
First used in [[w:1920|1920]]'s from the presumed effects of [[swim]]ming or wading across the [[w:Rio Grande|Rio Grande]]. Used by the U.S. Government in 1954 with [[w:Operation Wetback|Operation Wetback]].

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{derogatory}} a [[Mexican]] or Central American who [[illegal]]ly enters the [[United States of America]] from its southern border, often by either 
# {{derogatory}} anyone of the [[Mestizo]] race, used interchangeably with the [[Spanish language|Spanish]] term, ''[[mojado]]''.

